  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Le Val Thorens is a great addition to our collection. A modern and warm hotel, with great facilities and an even better location. </p>
<h2>Excellent Location </h2>
<p>Hotel Le Val Thorens is a firm favourite due to its fantastic location. This hotel is situated on the <a data-udi="umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8}" title="Val Thorens">Val Thorens</a> piste with ski-in, ski-out access, meaning skiing the whole of the <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys ski area</a> is super accessible and easy. Pop your skis on at the door and ski down for around 2 minutes to reach the lifts and the ski school meeting point.</p>
<h2>Spa and Relaxation</h2>
<p>If you like an hour or two to unwind in the evenings after a day on the slopes, you're in luck. There's a fabulous heated indoor swimming pool for you to use, with views of the surrounding mountains. The hotels spa area also has a sauna and steam room to really help relax those muscles after big ski days. </p>
<h2>Restaurants and Bars</h2>
<p>There are two restaurants on site, “Le Val Thorens” and the Savoyard “La Fondue” to fulfil any cheese lover’s desire, both having vintage and warm décor to cosy into. Le 1971 bar has a fireplace and music to listen to whilst sipping on a cocktail, or on a sunny day go out to the terrace and take in the mountain views. </p>]]></description>
